words: Back in my high school, the last person to get into Stanford, like twenty-one
years ago so it's a pretty big deal. And I didn't think I had any shot at all so I
was super surprised. And just the whole month went since I submitted my application I was just so
worried cause I was thinking I'm not going to get in and then it's going to be so embarrassing because like everyone
expects that I'm going to um... so I was
really, really nervous, but that made getting in all the better. So the night um
results were supposed to come back, my mom took me to Target, and she was just trying to distract me. Um I
was so nervous. And then I got back and I checked the email and it was my whole family was there and my
friend Nina. Um and I just... I wasn't even expecting it, but I
started crying like I didn't realize how much pressure I had been putting on myself for so many
years. Um like everything I had done. Like all the late night studying,
and like doing all these activities and it just felt like a huge load off my shoulders and I couldn't
believe it. Um and it was just an amazing, amazing feeling.
And turns out my parents had like bought me a cake and um gotten me a Stanford
sweatshirt ah which was really nice of them to have that much faith in me. Um...
